From Stanley Uzoaru, Owerri Barely 24 hours that the convoy of the former Governor of Imo State, Mr. Ikedi Ohakim, was attacked by gunmen, and four of his orderlies died in the process, a police post at Afor Atta in Njaba Local Government Area of the State has been set ablaze by gun welding miscreants. A source from the area told Daily Sun  that the incident happened last night as the hoodlums threw explosives into the premises of the station. No life was lost according to the source because none of the officers were on duty when the incident occurred. The  same police station was attacked in 2021.